This database is on MySQL AWS server so all you need to do is to make sure you have MySQL on the computer. 
If you don't have, please download it from the website provided as follows:

1. Download mysql workbench(a unified visual tool)here:
https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/workbench/

2.Install mysql workbench, open it and come to the MySQL Connection section. 

3. Click + (close to MySQL Connections) to connect to my database.

4. Input database information:

Connection name: Elixr_guest
Hostname: clinical-trial-criteria.c5gnhosuqybj.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com
Port: 3306
Username: guest
Password: guest@123

There are two schemas in this database. 
One is called criteria, including all the criteria information with trial information of Alzheimer's disease. 
The other one is called CLINICALTRIAL, including the introduction information (without criteria) of the entire disease spectrum at CT.gov.

